{"lemma":"شَجَّة","slug":"شَجَّة","root":"ش.ج.ج","root_slug":"ش-ج-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ج-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21704","n21707"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21704","headword_ar":"شَجَّهُ","root":"$j","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the former reg., (Msb,) [the latter irreg.,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~N","text_ar":"شَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to cleave its skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] namely, another's head: (S, * K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he clave his skin of the face"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he clave its skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the skin of the face or of the head: (Msb:) originally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struck it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the head,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to wound it and cleave it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and then used in relation to other members: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~ahu fiY raA^osihi","text_ar":"شَجَّهُ فِى رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY wajohihi","text_ar":"فِى وَجْهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he wounded him so as to cleave the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the flesh in his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Accord. to some, [contr. to the authority of the A,] it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~ati Als~afiynapu Alb~Hora","text_ar":"شَجَّتِ السَّفِينَةُ البّحْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. below]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$uj~u biyadK wayaA^osuw biA^uxoraY","text_ar":"يَشُجُّ بِيَدٍ وَيَاْسُو بِاُخْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one breaks a head with one hand and cures with another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one corrupts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mars, one time, and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1505},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rectifies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repairs, another time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN ya$uj~u mar~apF wayaA^osuw mar~apF","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ يَشُجُّ مَرَّةً وَيَاْسُو مَرَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd does,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"says, wrong one time, and right one time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~ati Als~afiynapu AlbaHora","text_ar":"شَجَّتِ السَّفِينَةُ البَحْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ship clave the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb:) and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~a AlbaHora","text_ar":"شَجَّ البَحْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he clave the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) said of a swimmer. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~a AlmafaAzapa","text_ar":"شَجَّ المَفَازَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He traversed the desert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~a AlA^aroDa biraAHilatihi","text_ar":"شَجَّ الاَرْضَ بِرَاحِلَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He traversed the land, with his camel that he rode, at a vehement rate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~a Al$~araAba","text_ar":"شَجَّ الشَّرَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~a Alxamora biAlmaA='","text_ar":"شَجَّ الخَمْرَ بِالمَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~N","text_ar":"شَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as above,] (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He mixed the beverage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fakaAna ya$uij~u EalaY~a misokFA","text_ar":"فَكَانَ يَشُِجُّ عَلَىَّ مِسْكًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And it was as though it mixed with her odour of musk the breath of wind that reached my organ of smell."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","A","L"]},{"entry_id":"n21707","headword_ar":"شَجَّةٌ","root":"$j","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of breaking"},{"kind":"text","text":"of one's head ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to cleave its skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its flesh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wound by which the head is broken"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * L, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to cleave its skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wound in the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAjN","text_ar":"شِجَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~aAtN","text_ar":"شَجَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) What are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAj","text_ar":"شِجَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"are of ten different kinds, (A, L,) distinguished by the following epithets: [1]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAriSapN","text_ar":"حَارِصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which peels off the [external] skin, but does not bring blood: [2]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAmiyapN","text_ar":"دَامِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which brings blood: [3]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baADiEapN","text_ar":"بَاضِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which cleaves the flesh slightly, and brings blood, but does not make it to flow: (but in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmg","text_ar":"دمغ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAmigapN","text_ar":"دَامِغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., what are here mentioned as the second and third are transposed:) 4,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutalaAHimapN","text_ar":"مُتَلَاحِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] which cleaves the flesh much: [5]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoHaAqN","text_ar":"سِمْحَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which leaves between it and the bone only a thin skin: these are five"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jAj","text_ar":"شجاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"for which there is no retaliation nor any determinate mulct, but respecting which a judge must give his sentence: [6]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwDiHapN","text_ar":"مُوضِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which reaches to the bone, and for which the mulct is five camels: [7]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA$imapN","text_ar":"هَاشِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which breaks the bone, and for which the mulct is ten camels: [8]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munaq~ilapN","text_ar":"مُنَقِّلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from which bone is removed, from one place to another, and for which the mulct is fifteen camels: [9]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^omuwmapN","text_ar":"مَاْمُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=m~apN","text_ar":"ا=مَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which leaves between it and the brain only a thin skin, and for which the mulct is one third of the whole price of blood: [10]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAmigapN","text_ar":"دَامِغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which reaches the brain, and for which the mulct is also one third of the whole price of blood. (L.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aj~ap","text_ar":"شَجَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of 'Abd-El-Hameed, [who was the goodliest man of his age,] the son of 'Abd-Allah the son of 'Omar the son of El-Khattáb, was the subject of a prov. on account of its beauty [and is said to have increased his goodliness]. (MF.)"}],"source_refs":["L","S","A","Msb"]}]}}